				<td colspan="2"><span>As said the mez being resisted is based on MR, if a chanter tashes or you actually have time to HoS before each mez they land a LOT better, the charisma as stated makes a HUGE difference for both missed notes but even more so with crit fails on lulls (310 char buffed, 265 unbuffed, tested at dif amounts from 200 up, every 10 points or so is noticable for crit fails).  The reason you probably have more trouble when they pull 5 mobs is because that means you are mezzing 4, same as doing a 4 song twist... just one or 2 missed notes, or a single resist really messes you up.  I can only keep 4 mobs completely locked down (high level mobs) if they are tashed, otherwise one will eventually resist and then they all start breaking free as I try to regain the chain.  I have JF2 also, and it does seem to help a little bit, just as leveling up a level helps a little bit.  But a nice Tash helps a LOT more.</span></td>
