				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Mez resists<a name="69423"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Nov 10 04 11:00 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span><blockquote><b>Quote:</b><br><span class="quote">Cause chanters can take a beating about as well as a wet paper bag, and in places like BoT and normal LDoNs its not uncommon to find a tank that may take awhile pulling taunt from the chanty. At least this way the chanty only dies every other pull instead of every pull when you get a bad tank.</span></blockquote> 
<br />

<br />
I seem to differ.
<br />

<br />
Chanters have nice tools to mez ANY mob (including 1K KT or MPG hitters). 
<br />

<br />
Sure, they can&#180;t tank worth much, BUT they have a nice 4.5K HP buffer thru runes (a 2K one and a 1.5K AA rune that&#180;s instant cast), and on top of that they have Boggle (-500 on mob&#180;s hate list, 0.5 sec cast). While runed chanters get virtually no interrupts.
<br />

<br />
Add to that the new Mind over Matter AA (50% off all melee DMG taken off your manapool instead of HPs), Stasis AA (Unresistable mez), and Soothing Words AA (instant deagro), and chanters are pretty set. In fact, if you look at the chanter board, most don&#180;t whine about dying all the time due to mez resists (some do though, there has to be whiners everywhere I guess. Maybe they Tash before mez or slow), what chanters whine about is the lack of mezzable content, and everything being single pulls, making playing a chanter pretty dull.
<br />

<br />
When I play my chanter I have no problems whatsoever mezzing, in fact when doing WoS mobs I request for adds on every pull, with 3 or 4 adds being cool, depending on tank (when doing KT or MPG, 1 add is usually ok, 2 adds is asking for it, and while ok, it might not be healthy for everyone, mainly tank).
<br />

<br />
When I play my bard, I bring 1 add tops, having 2 mob adds cuts down my bard group efficiency a lot, while having 1 add mezzed doesn&#180;t stop me from meleeing and buffing the group with 3 songs. So the mez is done on the pull mostly (specially on high end zones).
<br />

<br />
What really puzzles me about this thread is not why would a bard be helping with mezzing multiples if a chanter in group though (pre-bard mezzing is always nice to have around), but why would a 4 adds pull ever happen with a bard in group?
<br />

<br />
EDIT: Chanters also have an AE mez my bard really erally wants.</span></td>
